      "source": [
        "# Shark Attacks: A Global Exploratory Analysis\n",
        "\n",
        "An exploratory analysis of shark attack incidents recorded worldwide, examining\n",
        "how encounters vary across geography, activity, and time. This project moves past\n",
        "the tabloid framing of shark attacks to ask where and how risk actually concentrates —\n",
        "and where the data itself falls short."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "31e2e6f5",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "31e2e6f5"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Research Question\n",
        "How have shark attack patterns shifted across geography, activity, and time, and\n",
        "what factors are most associated with fatal outcomes?"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "208aefca",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "208aefca"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Dataset\n",
        "**`global_shark_attacks.csv`** (GSAF-derived)\n",
        "\n",
        "| Field | Description |\n",
        "|---|---|\n",
        "| `date` | Calendar date of the incident (where known). |\n",
        "| `year` | Year of incident, used for temporal analysis. |\n",
        "| `type` | Encounter classification: Unprovoked, Provoked, Boat, Sea Disaster, Invalid. |\n",
        "| `country` / `area` / `location` | Geographic hierarchy from country → specific beach. |\n",
        "| `activity` | Victim activity (surfing, swimming, fishing, diving). Free-text; needs normalization. |\n",
        "| `name` | Victim name, if recorded. |\n",
        "| `sex` / `age` | Victim demographics, often partially missing. |\n",
        "| `fatal_y_n` | Y/N flag indicating whether the encounter was fatal. |\n",
        "| `time` | Time of day (`HHhMM` format), frequently missing or approximate. |\n",
        "| `species` | Shark species, reported secondhand and inconsistently named. |"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "2edc85e5",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "2edc85e5"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Methodology\n",
        "1. **Inspect** — structural audit of shape, dtypes, and missingness before any transformation.\n",
        "2. **Clean** — normalize whitespace, parse dates, harmonize Y/N flags, coerce mixed types.\n",
        "3. **Feature engineer** — derive decade buckets, coarse species categories, and activity groups\n",
        "   from noisy free-text fields.\n",
        "4. **Univariate exploration** — distributions and value counts for each key field.\n",
        "5. **Temporal analysis** — attacks per year/decade, with explicit attention to reporting-coverage bias.\n",
        "6. **Geographic analysis** — country- and region-level concentrations.\n",
        "7. **Activity risk** — within-attack fatality rate by activity category (no population denominator).\n",
        "8. **Fatality correlates** — logistic regression with activity + species + country as features.\n",
        "9. **Findings + caveats** — surfaced honestly, not buried."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "82d3afb8",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "82d3afb8"
      },
      "source": [
